SQL Components
==============

General ODBC components to work with SQL Databases and all gory details therein.
The 'standard' proces to work with these components is:

// Define a database
SQLDatabase database;

// Go open the database from some ODBC datasource
database.Open("database","user","password");

if(database.IsOpen())
{
  // Get some meaningful SQL statement :-)
  CString query = "SELECT * FROM DUAL";

  // Grab a SQLQuery object, and connect to the database
  SQLQUery query(database);

  // Go run the statement
  query.DoSQLStatement(sql);

  // As long as we have a cursor running
  while(query.GetRecord())
  {
    // Grab a column
    SQLVariant* var = query.GetColumn(1);
    // Do something with it
    printf("The value is: %s",var.GetAsChar());
  }
}

// Go close it
// Or don't and just go out of scope
database.Close();


DATABASE INDEPENDENT
====================
You can use the following database types through the DBInfoDB class
- IBM Informix
- Oracle
- Microsoft SQL Server
- Microsoft Access (Jet engine)
- Firebird
- PostgreSQL
- Generic ODBC database

To do this, use the methods of "database->GetSQLInfo->SomeMethod()"
